# Project Memory

## Stack
- React + TypeScript (Vite)
- pnpm for package management
- Node v22 required (use `nvm use 22`)

## Rules (from AGENT.md + docs/)
- TypeScript everywhere — no .js/.jsx files
- Strict tsconfig: strict, noImplicitAny, strictNullChecks, noUncheckedIndexedAccess
- No caret/tilde in package.json versions (exact versions only)
- Use pnpm, not npm
- Functional style, immutable data (no mutation)
- Minimal dependencies

## Key files
- docs/engineering_principles.md — coding standards
- docs/agent_instructions.md — points to engineering_principles + ai_development_workflow
- docs/ai_development_workflow.md — dev loop and coding rules
- AGENT.md — tooling rules (node v22, pnpm, exact versions, .memory)
- CLAUDE.md — points to AGENT.md

## Project structure
- src/types.ts — shared interfaces (Entry, Mood, SubstanceEntry)
- src/constants.ts — MOODS, ANXIETY_LABELS, PRESETS, STORAGE_KEY
- src/storage.ts — loadEntries / saveEntries (localStorage)
- src/App.tsx — tab state + entry list
- src/components/LogTab.tsx — log form
- src/components/TrendsTab.tsx — chart + AI analysis + entry list

## Dev workflow
Always read CLAUDE.md → AGENT.md → docs/ before writing code.
Run `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit` to verify before finishing.
